A short itinerary is mentioned below. Itinerary can also be customised to match interest and time.    Shillong  03 Nights   04 Days  Day 01   Shillong Airport  SHL    Guwahati Airport  GAU    Railway Station  GHY   Kamakhya Station  KYQ    Shillong  On arrival and drive to Shillong. Enroute visit Umiam Lake and Don Bosco Museum. Check in at hotel and relax.  Overnight at Shillong.  Day 02   Shillong   Cherrapunjee Sohra    Shillong After breakfast drive to Cherrapunjee Sohra . Enrote to Sohra visit Elephant Falls and Dwang sing view Point. The road to Sohra is full mesmerizing views. You just need to eyes and mind open for it.  At Sohra visit Nohkalikai Falls  Seven Sister Falls and Arwah Cave   Mausmai Cave. Later drive back to Shillong. Overnight at Shillong.  Day 03   Shillong   Dawki   Mawlynnong   Shillong  After breakfast excursion to Dawki and Mawlynnong 3Hrs One way . Dawki is border village on the India   Bangladesh Border. You can visit the India Bangladesh border or take a boat ride on Umngot River. Umngot river is famous for its crystal clear water. The river flows from India to Bangladesh. Later take your lunch at Mawlynnong and visit the Living Root Bridge  Sky view and Balacing rock. Drive back to Shillong before sunset. Overnight at Shillong.   Day 04   Guwahati Half Day   Drop at Guwahati Airport  GAU    Railway Station  GHY   Kamakhya Station  KYQ  After breakfast check out of hotel and visit Maa Kamakhya Temple If time permits  Later drop to Airport   Railway Station for your journey back home. Captions: SHOCKER FROM NORTHEAST  FORMER MISS INDIA FINALIST RE ARRESTED AFTER BAIL FOR RUNNING OVER 8 ROAD WORKERS   INJURING 1 WHOSE LEGS HAD TO BE AMPUTATED   The Assam police today arrested a former Miss India finalist who was granted bail within 24 hours of knocking down nine people with her car in Guwahati on October 2.  A senior police officer said Rajkanya Baruah was booked under Section 308 of the Indian Penal Code for an attempt to commit culpable homicide. The punishment under this section is jail up to seven years or fine or both.  The 29 year old model was arrested within minutes of a medical board of the Gauhati Medical College and Hospital had found her in fine health. She had checked into the intensive care unit of a private hospital citing poor health after the police had summoned her on Tuesday.   The medical board said she is fit to appear before the investigating officer and needs no hospitalisation   Deputy Commissioner of Police Subhrajit Bora told journalists.  Rajkanya Baruah knocked down eight road workers while allegedly driving under the influence of alcohol at about 2 a.m. on October 2 in violation of night curfew due to the COVID 19 situation. She also ran over the lower part of a ninth person  identified as Joseph  whose legs had to be amputated.  Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma ordered a re investigation into the case after her bail triggered outrage across Assam. Two Sub Inspectors were accordingly  closed  to the police reserve for letting her get away lightly on bailable charges.  The police said Rajkanya Baruah has had brushes with the law in the past. There were two FIRs against her for knocking down an ex MLA s son with her car over a quarrel in 2017  and fighting with on duty police officials in front of a pub in 2018.  In 2015  she had spent a night at the Latasil Police Station for smashing liquor bottles near the Raj Bhavan. Captions: It was on the 24th of November 1986 that Kiran Srivastava and Atul Saxena  amidst their chosen friends and family  got married  envisaging a life  full of love and association that should have ideally lasted forever.  Though dimensions apart now  I would like to take this opportunity to wish this special couple a very happy 35th anniversary.   I want to thank them for raising such a deceptively handsome  honestly benevolent and thoroughly empathizing gentleman  who understands how to emotionally differentiate the  actual  wrong from the socially  accepted  right  someone who values the freedom to commit his own mistakes and subsequently learns from them  someone who appreciates the beauty of calculative risks   yearns it s payoffs  to most importantly  becoming a kind hearted person who cares for his fellow beings without grudging a reason or an agenda.  Without the two of you  I would never have had the world s most scrupulous support system to lean on  I would not have anyone to solemnly face the wrath for my severely made mistakes.   Without you two  I would not have such a wonderful life.  No letter and no amount of thank you s will ever be able to put into words how much the two of you mean to me.  Happy anniversary Maa and Paa.

Demojized: Just posted a photo @ Sri Sankardev High School
Captions: divitfoundation organised a cycle rally cum clean up drive at Sri Sankardev High School today to mark  goldenjubilee of 1971 war victory. Students of class 10th were enthusiastic and cooperative throughout the event. The event began with a Cycle rally  flagged off by teacher Sri Jiten ji. This event coincided with the launch of our project AWAS  All Waste Awareness Seminar   the volunteers demonstrated the collection and segregation of Dry waste to the students   faculty members present. Complying with Covid protocol laid down by the govt. Volunteers distributed hand gloves   gash bags to the Students to collect Wet Dry  plastic wrappers  plastic bottle and glass items separately. The event was graced by a special guest Sri Dhiren Chandra Sarma who served in the  indianarmy during the war. The Chief Guest proudly talked about his experience with The Army   encouraged the young students to pursue a career in the Military. He also appreciated our initiative in waste management . This event was wrapped up by singing Jaatiyo geet   Rastra gaan  that was followed by the distribution of healthy refreshments. we thank our v  divitfoundation.india  for giving us this opportunity for a grand occasion.                     pragnewsofficial  protidin24  newsliveghy  guwahati municipal corporation  nehru yuva kendra sangathan

Demojized: Just posted a photo @ House no 39 Handloom Hues
Captions: Barnali Baishya  Is wearing a beautiful rose pink Mekhela Sador  with Guna and eriwork. Photography by Bikash Sarma.  Make up by Manika Sarma Jewelry by Aparajita  Mekhela Sador by Handloom Hues   My Mom s Sari Pallu    I don t think our kids know what a pallu is as mothers now rarely wear saree. The principle use of Ma s pallu was to provide the elegance to her drape. But along with that  it also served as a potholder for removing hot pans from the stove.  It was wonderful for drying children s tears  and on occasion was even used for cleaning out dirty ears and as a hand towel.  For sleeping kids her lap was the mattress and her pallu the warm cover.  When company came  those pallus were ideal hiding places for shy kids.. And when going out as little kids  the pallu became an anchor  a guide to follow the Mom in the big bad world  And when the weather was cold  Maa  wrapped it around her arms.  Those glorious sari pallus wiped many a perspiring brow  bent over the hot wood stove.  Chips and kindling wood were brought into the kitchen in that pallu. It doubled as her apron too  From the garden  it carried all sorts of vegetables. After the peas had been shelled  it carried out the hulls.  In the fall  the pallu was used to bring in berries and sweet scented flowers that had fallen from the trees.  When unexpected company drove up the road  it was surprising how much furniture that old sari pallu could dust in a matter of seconds. It carried so many toys  a proper basket  It will be a long time before someone invents something that will replace that  old time sari pallu  that served so many purposes.  The pallu is nothing but magic woven.   And know what this pallu carried.....I don t think I ever caught anything from my MOMS pallu   but love  Author unknown

Demojized: Just posted a photo @ Tatynpobka tattoos
Captions: Never did I think I would get inked for someone other than my parents but just like our relationship  unique things kept on happening to us as we matured together from being friends to partners and he being my protector  my guide and my guardian angel since the very first day  just like my father.A Leo does need care  protection and adulation and what better than a Saggitarius to do so... Thank you for always being there and for everything.
